{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":392,"text":"I'm almost like a crazy evangelical."},{"time":2586,"text":"I've always known that the age of design is upon us,"},{"time":5331,"text":"almost like a rapture."},{"time":7412,"text":"If the day is sunny, I think,"},{"time":8947,"text":"\"Oh, the gods have had a good design day.\""},{"time":11472,"text":"Or, I go to a show and I see a beautiful piece by an artist,"},{"time":15788,"text":"particularly beautiful, I say"},{"time":17090,"text":"he's so good because he clearly looked to design"},{"time":20090,"text":"to understand what he needed to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21813,"text":"So I really do believe that design"},{"time":24514,"text":"is the highest form of creative expression."},{"time":27276,"text":"That's why I'm talking to you today about the age of design,"},{"time":30986,"text":"and the age of design is the age in which design"},{"time":33181,"text":"is still cute furniture, is still posters,"},{"time":37020,"text":"is still fast cars, what you see at MoMA today."},{"time":39878,"text":"But in truth, what I really would like to explain"},{"time":43703,"text":"to the public and to the audiences of MoMA is that"},{"time":46005,"text":"the most interesting chairs are the ones"},{"time":48668,"text":"that are actually made by a robot,"},{"time":51545,"text":"like this beautiful chair by Dirk Vander Kooij,"},{"time":54326,"text":"where a robot deposits a toothpaste-like slur"},{"time":58058,"text":"of recycled refrigerator parts,"},{"time":60914,"text":"as if he were a big candy, and makes a chair out of it."},{"time":65382,"text":"Or good design is digital fonts that we use all the time"},{"time":69017,"text":"and that become part of our identity."},{"time":71146,"text":"I want people to understand"},{"time":72866,"text":"that design is so much more than cute chairs,"},{"time":76081,"text":"that it is first and foremost everything that is around us"},{"time":79548,"text":"in our life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81137,"text":"And it's interesting how so much of what we're talking about"},{"time":83970,"text":"tonight is not simply design but interaction design."},{"time":87146,"text":"And in fact, interaction design is what I've been trying"},{"time":91023,"text":"to insert in the collection of the Museum of Modern Art"},{"time":93401,"text":"for a few years, starting not very timidly"},{"time":96365,"text":"but just pointedly with works, for instance,"},{"time":99139,"text":"by Martin Wattenberg -- the way a machine"},{"time":101700,"text":"plays chess with itself, that you see here,"},{"time":104644,"text":"or Lisa Strausfeld and her partners, the Sugar interface"},{"time":108108,"text":"for One Laptop Per Child,"},{"time":110218,"text":"Toshio Iwai's Tenori-On musical instruments,"},{"time":114072,"text":"and Philip Worthington's Shadow Monsters,"},{"time":117284,"text":"and John Maeda's Reactive Books,"},{"time":119740,"text":"and also Jonathan Harris and Sep Kamvar's I Want You To Want Me."},{"time":123905,"text":"These were some of the first acquisitions that really"},{"time":126596,"text":"introduced the idea of interaction design to the public."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129780,"text":"But more recently, I've been trying really to go even deeper"},{"time":134019,"text":"into interaction design with examples"},{"time":136252,"text":"that are emotionally really suggestive"},{"time":138995,"text":"and that really explain interaction design at a level"},{"time":141700,"text":"that is almost undeniable."},{"time":143771,"text":"The Wind Map, by Wattenberg and Fernanda Viégas,"},{"time":146851,"text":"I don't know if you've ever seen it -- it's really fantastic."},{"time":149267,"text":"It looks at the territory of the United States"},{"time":151789,"text":"as if it were a wheat field that is procured by the winds"},{"time":157514,"text":"and that is really giving you a pictorial image"},{"time":160687,"text":"of what's going on with the winds in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163911,"text":"But also, more recently, we started acquiring video games,"},{"time":168530,"text":"and that's where all hell broke loose"},{"time":171073,"text":"in a really interesting way. (Laughter)"},{"time":173241,"text":"There are still people that believe that there's a high and there's a low."},{"time":175921,"text":"And that's really what I find so intriguing"},{"time":178895,"text":"about the reactions that we've had to the anointment"},{"time":183444,"text":"of video games in the MoMA collection."},{"time":185680,"text":"We've -- No, first of all, New York Magazine always gets it."},{"time":188967,"text":"I love them. So we are in the right quadrant."},{"time":191112,"text":"We are in the Highbrow -- that's daring, that's courageous --"},{"time":195346,"text":"and Brilliant, which is great."},{"time":196769,"text":"Timidly, we've been higher on the diagonal in other situations,"},{"time":200105,"text":"but it's okay. It's good. It's good. It's good. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203472,"text":"But here comes the art critic. Oh, that was fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206600,"text":"So the first was Jonathan Jones from The Guardian."},{"time":208816,"text":"\"Sorry, MoMA, video games are not art.\""},{"time":211484,"text":"Did I ever say they were art? I was talking about interaction design. Excuse me."},{"time":215769,"text":"\"Exhibiting Pac-Man and Tetris alongside Picasso and Van Gogh\" --"},{"time":219576,"text":"They're two floors away. (Laughter) —"},{"time":222736,"text":"\"will mean game over for any real understanding of art.\""},{"time":227404,"text":"I'm bringing in the end of the world. You know?"},{"time":231379,"text":"We were talking about the rapture? It's coming."},{"time":233216,"text":"And Jonathan Jones is making it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235953,"text":"So the same Guardian rebuts,"},{"time":238727,"text":"\"Are video games art: the debate that shouldn't be."},{"time":241466,"text":"Last week, Guardian art critic blah blah suggested"},{"time":244055,"text":"that games cannot qualify as art. But is he right?"},{"time":247369,"text":"And does it matter?\" Thank you. Does it matter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249844,"text":"You know, it's like once again there's this whole problem"},{"time":252585,"text":"of design being often misunderstood for art,"},{"time":255537,"text":"or the idea that is so diffuse that designers want to"},{"time":259404,"text":"aspire to, would like to be called, artists."},{"time":262729,"text":"No. Designers aspire to be really great designers."},{"time":266041,"text":"Thank you very much. And that's more than enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267954,"text":"So my knight in shining armor, John Maeda,"},{"time":271441,"text":"without any prompt, came out with this big declaration"},{"time":274943,"text":"on why video games belong in the MoMA."},{"time":277313,"text":"And that was fantastic. And I thought that was it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279473,"text":"But then there was another wonderfully pretentious article"},{"time":283129,"text":"that came out in The New Republic, so pretentious,"},{"time":286177,"text":"by Liel Leibovitz, and it said, \"MoMA has mistaken video games for art.\" Again."},{"time":290137,"text":"\"The museum is putting Pac-Man alongside Picasso.\" Again."},{"time":293557,"text":"\"That misses the point.\""},{"time":294676,"text":"Excuse me. You're missing the point."},{"time":296534,"text":"And here, look, the above question is put bluntly:"},{"time":300582,"text":"\"Are video games art? No. Video games aren't art"},{"time":303932,"text":"because they are quite thoroughly something else: code.\""},{"time":308453,"text":"Oh, so Picasso is not art because it's oil paint. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312004,"text":"So it's so fantastic to see"},{"time":314234,"text":"how these feathers that were ruffled,"},{"time":317430,"text":"and these reactions, were so vehement."},{"time":319496,"text":"And you know what?"},{"time":320555,"text":"The International Cat Video Film Festival"},{"time":323072,"text":"didn't have that much of a reaction. (Laughter)"},{"time":325505,"text":"I think this was truly fantastic."},{"time":327244,"text":"We were talking about dancing ponies, but I was really jealous"},{"time":330219,"text":"of the Walker Arts Center for putting up this festival,"},{"time":333535,"text":"because it's very, very wonderful."},{"time":335919,"text":"And there's this Flaubert quote that I love:"},{"time":338859,"text":"\"I have always tried to live in an ivory tower,"},{"time":340804,"text":"but a tide of shit is beating at its walls,"},{"time":343164,"text":"threatening to undermine it.\""},{"time":345110,"text":"I consider myself the tide of shit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347255,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352899,"text":"You know, we have to go through that."},{"time":354589,"text":"Even in the 1930s, my colleagues"},{"time":357365,"text":"that were trying to put together an abstract art show"},{"time":359890,"text":"had all of these works stopped by the customs officers"},{"time":362887,"text":"that decided they were not art."},{"time":364891,"text":"So it's happened before, and it will happen in the future,"},{"time":367459,"text":"but right now I can tell you that I am so, so proud"},{"time":371739,"text":"to be able to call Pac-Man part of the MoMA collection."},{"time":375963,"text":"And the same with, for instance, Tetris, original version, the Soviet one."},{"time":381356,"text":"And you know, the amount of work --"},{"time":383882,"text":"yeah, Alexey Pajitnov was working for the Soviet government"},{"time":387471,"text":"and that's how he developed Tetris,"},{"time":389325,"text":"and Alexey himself reconstructed the whole game"},{"time":393211,"text":"and even gave us a simulation of the cathode ray tube"},{"time":396949,"text":"that makes it look slightly bombed."},{"time":400460,"text":"And it's fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401964,"text":"So behind these acquisitions is an enormous amount of work,"},{"time":405128,"text":"because we're still the Museum of Modern Art,"},{"time":406531,"text":"so even when we tackle popular culture,"},{"time":408238,"text":"we tackle it as a form of interaction design"},{"time":411367,"text":"and as something that has to go into the collection at MoMA,"},{"time":413517,"text":"therefore, has to be researched."},{"time":415581,"text":"So to get to choosing Eric Chahi's"},{"time":418531,"text":"wonderful Another World, amongst others,"},{"time":421179,"text":"we put together a panel of experts,"},{"time":422859,"text":"and we worked on this acquisition,"},{"time":424369,"text":"and it's mostly myself and Kate Carmody and Paul Galloway."},{"time":427876,"text":"We worked on it for a year and a half."},{"time":430125,"text":"So many people helped us — designers of games,"},{"time":433098,"text":"you might know Jamin Warren"},{"time":435268,"text":"and his collaborators at Kill Screen magazine,"},{"time":437756,"text":"and you know, Kevin Slavin. You name it."},{"time":439488,"text":"We bugged everybody, because we knew that we were ignorant."},{"time":442752,"text":"We were not real gamers enough,"},{"time":444898,"text":"so we had to really talk to them."},{"time":446954,"text":"And so we decided, of course, to have Sim City 2000,"},{"time":450515,"text":"not the other Sim City, that one in particular,"},{"time":453443,"text":"so the criteria that we developed along the way"},{"time":456442,"text":"were really strong, and were not only criteria of selection."},{"time":459691,"text":"They were also criteria of exhibition and of preservation."},{"time":463875,"text":"That's what makes this acquisition more than a little game"},{"time":467178,"text":"or a little joke. It's truly a way to think of how to preserve"},{"time":471069,"text":"and show artifacts that will more and more"},{"time":473884,"text":"become part of our lives in the future."},{"time":475847,"text":"We live today, as you know very well, not in the digital,"},{"time":478899,"text":"not in the physical, but in the kind of minestrone"},{"time":482115,"text":"that our mind makes of the two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484155,"text":"And that's really where interaction lies,"},{"time":487284,"text":"and that's the importance of interaction."},{"time":489539,"text":"And in order to explain interaction, we need to really"},{"time":492683,"text":"bring people in and make them realize"},{"time":495324,"text":"how interaction is part of their lives."},{"time":497030,"text":"So when I talk about it, I don't talk only about video games,"},{"time":499859,"text":"which are in a way the purest form of interaction,"},{"time":502372,"text":"unadulterated by any kind of function or finality."},{"time":505844,"text":"I also talk about the MetroCard vending machine,"},{"time":508991,"text":"which I consider a masterpiece of interaction."},{"time":511117,"text":"I mean, that interface is beautiful."},{"time":513428,"text":"It looks like a burly MTA guy coming out of the tunnel."},{"time":517005,"text":"You know, with your mitt you can actually paw"},{"time":520564,"text":"the MetroCard, and I talk about how bad"},{"time":523833,"text":"ATM machines usually are."},{"time":526894,"text":"So I let people understand that it's up to them"},{"time":529723,"text":"to know how to judge interaction"},{"time":531965,"text":"so as to know when it's good or when it's bad."},{"time":533992,"text":"So when I show The Sims,"},{"time":535645,"text":"I try to make people really feel what it meant"},{"time":539122,"text":"to have an interaction with The Sims,"},{"time":541021,"text":"not only the fun but also the responsibility"},{"time":543378,"text":"that came with the Tamagotchi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545253,"text":"You know, video games can be truly deep"},{"time":547133,"text":"even when they're completely mindless."},{"time":548877,"text":"I'm sure that all of you know Katamari Damacy."},{"time":551405,"text":"It's about rolling a ball and picking up as many objects as you can"},{"time":555126,"text":"in a finite amount of time"},{"time":556957,"text":"and hopefully you'll be able to make it into a planet."},{"time":559320,"text":"I've never made it into a planet, but that's it."},{"time":561565,"text":"Or, you know, Vib-Ribbon was not distributed here in the United States."},{"time":564733,"text":"It was a PlayStation game, but mostly for Japan."},{"time":566925,"text":"And it was one of the first video games"},{"time":568594,"text":"in which you could choose your own music."},{"time":570295,"text":"So you would put into the PlayStation,"},{"time":572617,"text":"you would put your own CD,"},{"time":574422,"text":"and then the game would change alongside your music. So really fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579184,"text":"Not to mention Eve Online."},{"time":580595,"text":"Eve Online is an artificial universe, if you wish,"},{"time":583676,"text":"but one of the diplomats that was killed in Benghazi,"},{"time":586229,"text":"not Ambassador Stevens, but one of his collaborators,"},{"time":588837,"text":"was a really big shot in Eve Online,"},{"time":590705,"text":"so here you have a diplomat in the real world"},{"time":593325,"text":"that spends his time in Eve Online"},{"time":595813,"text":"to kind of test, maybe, all of his ideas about diplomacy"},{"time":599982,"text":"and about universe-building, and to the point that"},{"time":602939,"text":"the first announcement of the bombing"},{"time":604949,"text":"was actually given on Eve Online,"},{"time":607365,"text":"and after his death, several parts of the universe"},{"time":609749,"text":"were named after him."},{"time":611209,"text":"And I was just recently at the Eve Online fan festival"},{"time":615043,"text":"in Reykjavík that was quite amazing."},{"time":617181,"text":"I mean, we're talking about an experience"},{"time":619733,"text":"that of course can seem weird to many,"},{"time":622525,"text":"but that is very educational."},{"time":624423,"text":"Of course, there are games that are even more educational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627296,"text":"Dwarf Fortress is like the holy grail"},{"time":629988,"text":"of this kind of massive multiplayer online game,"},{"time":632377,"text":"and in fact the two Adams brothers were in Reykjavík,"},{"time":634923,"text":"and they were greeted"},{"time":637557,"text":"by a standing ovation by all the Eve Online fans."},{"time":640765,"text":"It was amazing to see. And it's a beautiful game."},{"time":643357,"text":"So you start seeing here that"},{"time":645901,"text":"the aesthetics that are so important"},{"time":647661,"text":"to a museum collection like MoMA's"},{"time":649504,"text":"are kept alive also by the selection of these games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653165,"text":"And you know, Valve -- you know, Portal --"},{"time":655125,"text":"is an example of a video game in which"},{"time":657248,"text":"you have a certain type of violence"},{"time":659562,"text":"which also leads me to talk about"},{"time":661661,"text":"one of the biggest issues that we had to discuss"},{"time":664007,"text":"when we acquired the video games, what to do with violence."},{"time":666267,"text":"Right? We had to make decisions."},{"time":668671,"text":"At MoMA, interestingly, there's a lot of violence"},{"time":672229,"text":"depicted in the art part of the collection,"},{"time":675133,"text":"but when I came to MoMA 19 years ago, and as an Italian,"},{"time":678349,"text":"I said, \"You know what, we need a Beretta.\""},{"time":679900,"text":"And I was told, \"No. No guns in the design collection.\""},{"time":683013,"text":"And I was like, \"Why?\""},{"time":683945,"text":"Interestingly, I learned that it's considered"},{"time":687461,"text":"that in design and in the design collection,"},{"time":689211,"text":"what you see is what you get."},{"time":690448,"text":"So when you see a gun, it's an instrument for killing in the design collection."},{"time":694338,"text":"If it's in the art collection,"},{"time":695951,"text":"it might be a critique of the killing instrument."},{"time":699695,"text":"So it's very interesting."},{"time":701401,"text":"But we are acquiring our critical dimension also in design,"},{"time":704040,"text":"so maybe one day we'll be able to acquire also the guns."},{"time":706531,"text":"But here, in this particular case, we decided,"},{"time":709795,"text":"you know, with Kate and Paul,"},{"time":711078,"text":"that we would have no gratuitous violence."},{"time":713337,"text":"So we have Portal because you shoot walls"},{"time":716089,"text":"in order to create new spaces."},{"time":717409,"text":"We have Street Fighter II, because martial arts are good."},{"time":720514,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":722030,"text":"But we don't have GTA because,"},{"time":726132,"text":"maybe it's my own reflection,"},{"time":727739,"text":"I've never been able to do anything but crashing cars"},{"time":730122,"text":"and shooting prostitutes and pimps."},{"time":732082,"text":"So it was not very constructive. (Laughter)"},{"time":735623,"text":"So, I'm making fun of it, but we discussed this"},{"time":739869,"text":"for so many days. You have no idea."},{"time":742956,"text":"And to this day, I am ambivalent,"},{"time":745283,"text":"but when you have instead games like Flow, there's no doubt."},{"time":748699,"text":"It's like, it's about serenity and it's about sublime."},{"time":751899,"text":"It's about experiencing what it means to be a sea creature."},{"time":756185,"text":"Then we have a few also side-scrollers -- classical ones."},{"time":760010,"text":"So it's quite a hefty collection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761844,"text":"And right now, we started with the first 14,"},{"time":764102,"text":"but we have several that are coming up,"},{"time":765995,"text":"and the reason why we haven't acquired them yet"},{"time":767907,"text":"is because you don't acquire just the game."},{"time":770335,"text":"You acquire the relationship with the company."},{"time":772409,"text":"What we want, what we aspire to, is the code."},{"time":775507,"text":"It's very hard to get, of course."},{"time":776904,"text":"But that's what would enable us to preserve"},{"time":778777,"text":"the video games for a really long time,"},{"time":780766,"text":"and that's what museums do."},{"time":782039,"text":"They also preserve artifacts for posterity."},{"time":784640,"text":"In absence of the code, because, you know,"},{"time":787260,"text":"video game companies are not very forthcoming in some cases,"},{"time":791027,"text":"in absence of that, we acquire the relationship with the company."},{"time":794523,"text":"We're going to stay with them forever."},{"time":795803,"text":"They're not going to get rid of us."},{"time":797036,"text":"And one day, we'll get that code. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":800507,"text":"But I want to explain to you the criteria that we chose"},{"time":803675,"text":"for interaction design. Aesthetics are really important."},{"time":806697,"text":"And I'm showing you Core War here,"},{"time":808738,"text":"which is an early game that takes advantage aesthetically"},{"time":812053,"text":"of the limitations of the processor."},{"time":813874,"text":"So the kind of interferences that you see here"},{"time":817123,"text":"that look like beautiful barriers in the game"},{"time":819767,"text":"are actually a consequence of the processor's limitedness,"},{"time":824114,"text":"which is fantastic. So aesthetics is always important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827194,"text":"And so is space, the spatial aspect of games."},{"time":831198,"text":"You know, I feel that the best video games"},{"time":833342,"text":"are the ones that have really savvy architects"},{"time":836878,"text":"that are behind them, and if they're not architects,"},{"time":839501,"text":"bona fide trained in architecture, they have that feeling."},{"time":842139,"text":"But the spatial evolution in video games is extremely important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846227,"text":"Time. The way we experience time in video games,"},{"time":849187,"text":"as in other forms of interaction design,"},{"time":851969,"text":"is really quite amazing."},{"time":853228,"text":"It can be real time or it can be the time within the game,"},{"time":856233,"text":"as is in Animal Crossing, where seasons"},{"time":858449,"text":"follow each other at their own pace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861041,"text":"So time, space, aesthetics,"},{"time":864320,"text":"and then, most important, behavior."},{"time":866689,"text":"The real core issue of interaction design is behavior."},{"time":870809,"text":"Designers that deal with interaction design behaviors"},{"time":874286,"text":"that go to influence the rest of our lives."},{"time":876601,"text":"They're not just limited to our interaction with the screen."},{"time":879136,"text":"In this case, I'm showing you Marble Madness,"},{"time":881185,"text":"which is a beautiful game"},{"time":882386,"text":"in which the controller is a big sphere that vibrates with you,"},{"time":885657,"text":"so you have a sphere that's moving in this landscape,"},{"time":888090,"text":"and the sphere, the controller itself, gives you a sense of the movement."},{"time":892622,"text":"In a way, you can see how video games"},{"time":894977,"text":"are the purest aspect of interaction design"},{"time":897689,"text":"and are very useful to explain what interaction is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902308,"text":"We don't want to show the video games"},{"time":904393,"text":"with the paraphernalia. No arcade nostalgia."},{"time":907335,"text":"If anything, we want to show the code,"},{"time":909017,"text":"and here you see Ben Fry's distellamap of Pac-Man,"},{"time":912031,"text":"of the Pac-Man code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913520,"text":"So the way we acquired the games is very interesting"},{"time":917859,"text":"and very unorthodox. You see them here"},{"time":920055,"text":"displayed alongside other examples of design,"},{"time":924063,"text":"furniture and other parts,"},{"time":925673,"text":"but there's no paraphernalia, no nostalagia,"},{"time":928901,"text":"only the screen and a little shelf with the controllers."},{"time":931850,"text":"The controllers are, of course, part of the experience,"},{"time":933994,"text":"so you cannot do away with it."},{"time":936443,"text":"But interestingly, this choice was not condemned"},{"time":940941,"text":"too vehemently by gamers."},{"time":942286,"text":"I was afraid that they would kill us,"},{"time":943593,"text":"and instead they understood, especially"},{"time":945659,"text":"when I told them that I was trying to apply the same stratagem"},{"time":948363,"text":"that Philip Johnson applied in 1934"},{"time":951505,"text":"when he wanted to make people understand"},{"time":953547,"text":"the importance of design, and he took propeller blades"},{"time":955859,"text":"and pieces of machinery and"},{"time":958139,"text":"in the MoMA galleries he put them on white pedestals"},{"time":961266,"text":"against white walls, as if they were Brancusi sculptures."},{"time":964483,"text":"He created this strange distance, this shock,"},{"time":968211,"text":"that made people realize how gorgeous formally,"},{"time":971869,"text":"and also important functionally, design pieces were."},{"time":975637,"text":"I would like to do the same with video games."},{"time":977891,"text":"By getting rid of the sticky carpets and the cigarette butts"},{"time":980971,"text":"and everything else that we might remember from our childhood,"},{"time":983579,"text":"I want people to understand"},{"time":988150,"text":"that those are important forms of design."},{"time":990019,"text":"And in a way, the video games, the fonts and everything else"},{"time":993197,"text":"lead us to make people understand"},{"time":995881,"text":"a wider meaning for design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998223,"text":"One of my dream acquisitions,"},{"time":1000276,"text":"which has been on hold for a few years"},{"time":1002191,"text":"but now will come back on the front burner,"},{"time":1005193,"text":"is a 747."},{"time":1006625,"text":"I would like to acquire it, but without owning it."},{"time":1009563,"text":"I don't want it to be at MoMA and possessed by MoMA."},{"time":1012874,"text":"I want it to keep flying."},{"time":1014258,"text":"So it's an acquisition where MoMA makes an arrangement"},{"time":1017798,"text":"with an airline and keeps the Boeing 747 flying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022565,"text":"And the same with the \"@\" sign that we acquired a few years ago."},{"time":1025683,"text":"It was the first example of an acquisition of something"},{"time":1027865,"text":"that is in the public domain."},{"time":1029270,"text":"And what I say to people, it's almost as if"},{"time":1031030,"text":"a butterfly were flying by"},{"time":1033004,"text":"and we captured the shadow on the wall,"},{"time":1036153,"text":"and just we're showing the shadow."},{"time":1037610,"text":"So in a way, we're showing a manifestation"},{"time":1039818,"text":"of something that is truly important"},{"time":1042331,"text":"and that is part of our identity but that nobody can have."},{"time":1045962,"text":"And it's too long to explain the acquisition,"},{"time":1047898,"text":"but if you want to go on the MoMA blog,"},{"time":1050404,"text":"there's a long post where I explain why"},{"time":1052498,"text":"it's such a great example of design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054786,"text":"Along the way, I've had to burn a few chairs. You know?"},{"time":1058147,"text":"I've had to do away with a few concepts of design past."},{"time":1062466,"text":"But I see that people are coming along,"},{"time":1065282,"text":"that the audiences, paradoxically,"},{"time":1067032,"text":"are much more responsive and much more understanding"},{"time":1069858,"text":"of this expansion of design than some of my colleagues are."},{"time":1073916,"text":"Design is truly everywhere,"},{"time":1075443,"text":"and design is as important as anything,"},{"time":1078411,"text":"and I'm so glad that, because of its diversity"},{"time":1080871,"text":"and because of its centrality to our lives,"},{"time":1083186,"text":"many more people are coming to it"},{"time":1084914,"text":"as a profession, as a passion,"},{"time":1087003,"text":"and as, very simply, part of their own culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089977,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}